title: For Sale:  Colt 1908 - Original Grips and Magazine
postcontent:
I am offering  a Colt Vest Pocket Hammerless Automatic model 1908 25cal.(model N). Mfg in 1918 for your consideration.

For those that have never owned a Colt pistol produced in the early 1900's, you're really missing out. These guns were hand crafted and polished by highly skilled craftsmen long before the days of CNC machines, plastic parts and mass production methods robbed firearms of their personality. Most collectors agree that this era was the pinnacle of Colt's production quality. 

CONDITION: All original parts and finish. The frame has retained most of its beautiful original charcoal bluing with the frontstrap and trigger guard showing some patina. The frame overall shows some light freckling with no significant pitting or dents/dings. The original case colors are still bright on trigger and visible on the grip safety, safety and mag release. The slide shows a little more wear on the finish (too much time in it's holster) Much of its bluing is wearing thin and there is scattered freckling and patina throughout. No significant pitting or dents/dings. The bore looks good with well-defined rifling, and only very light pitting on first 1/3rd of bore. There is light pitting and some patina in the chamber of the bore. The original grips are in excellent condition with no significant wear and no cracks or chips. The magazine is the original two-tone, pinned magazine correctly showing no caliber marking on baseplate. It is in excellent condition showing almost no wear. 

FUNCTION: The slide/frame fit is still very tight, The springs are still strong and the action is smooth. Mechanically the pistol is in excellent shape. It functioned flawlessly at the range, and its' accuracy is still surprisingly good for a near antique pocket pistol. 

OVERALL ASSESSMENT: While not a safe-queen, this pistol is in very good shape and is still very collectible. The wear that it does show appears to be from honest use. I see no indications of misuse or abuse. This is a great opportunity to buy a 93 year old collectible Colt at a reasonable price that you wouldn't be apprehensive about taking to the range and enjoying.

I travel between Cinicinnati, Columbus and Dayton weekly and can meet you most places in-between.  I can be flexible on the timing as well.

Cash only and you must be willing to fill out a private bill of sale for my records.  I am not interested in trades at this time.


Thanks,
Brad Clissold
REDACTED.
